Senate President Ahmad Lawan says the National Assembly will pass the 2020 Appropriation Bill on November 28, 2019. The Senate president stated this at plenary yesterday. He called on the Senate Committee on Appropriation to lay its reports by November 26. “It now behoves on the Committee on Appropriation to work very hard and ensure that the report is ready for laying by November 26 to pass the appropriation on 28th of November”, he said. He commended all the committees for working hard to ensure that the budget worked within a defined parameter. Senate insists on passing 2020 budget by Nov 28 BREAKING: N'Assembly mulls passage of 2020 budget Nov 28 Nigeria must not continue borrowing — Senate president Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.